## 2Ô∏è‚É£ üîç Verify Installations

Open Terminal and verify:

```bash
go version
node -v
npm -v
psql --version
git --version

/Each command must return a version number.
If any command fails, install the missing software before proceeding./

## 3Ô∏è‚É£ Project Overview

Backend (Go + Gin + GORM)
backend/
  config/
  controllers/
  middleware/
  models/
  routes/
  main.go

Completed Features:
- PostgreSQL database connection
- User model
- Password hashing (bcrypt)
- JWT authentication
- Register endpoint
- Login endpoint
- Clean routing structure
- dev branch created
- main branch protected

Available API Endpoints
  POST /api/auth/register
  POST /api/auth/login

Backend runs on: http://localhost:8080

Frontend (React + Vite)
Structure:
  frontend/
  src/
  public/
  package.json

Installed:
 - React
 - Vite
 - Axios
 - React Router DOM

Frontend runs on: http://localhost:5173

4Ô∏è‚É£ Clone Repository (macOS)

Open Terminal:
  cd ~/Documents
  git clone https://github.com/rebatidas/TheNucleus.git
  cd TheNucleus

Switch to development branch:
  git checkout dev

5Ô∏è‚É£ Open Project in VS Code

If VS Code CLI is enabled:

code .


If not:

Open VS Code ‚Üí File ‚Üí Open Folder ‚Üí Select TheNucleus

6Ô∏è‚É£ Database Setup (PostgreSQL)

Install PostgreSQL if not installed.
Create database: createdb TheNucleus

If that fails, open PostgreSQL manually and create a database named: TheNucleus

7Ô∏è‚É£ Backend Setup

Navigate to backend:
  cd backend
Install dependencies:
  go mod tidy


Open: backend/config/db.go
Update database password to match your local PostgreSQL password.
Run backend:
  go run main.go
Expected output:
  Database connected successfully
  Listening and serving HTTP on :8080

Test backend:
  Open browser: http://localhost:8080

8Ô∏è‚É£ Frontend Setup

Open a new terminal window.
Navigate to frontend:
  cd frontend
  npm install
  npm run dev

Open browser: http://localhost:5173

You should see the React starter screen.

9Ô∏è‚É£ Git Workflow (MANDATORY)

‚ùå Never push directly to main.

Always follow this workflow:

git checkout dev
git checkout -b feature/your-feature-name


After finishing work:

git add .
git commit -m "Feature description"
git push -u origin feature/your-feature-name


Create Pull Request ‚Üí merge into dev.

Only stable code moves from dev ‚Üí main.


| Service    | Port |
| ---------- | ---- |
| Backend    | 8080 |
| Frontend   | 5173 |
| PostgreSQL | 5432 |
